text:
on december 6, 1989, 14 female students and a female administrator at l'école polytechnique de montréal were murdered because they were women. the shocking impact of their deaths led parliament to designate december 6 as a national day of remembrance. nearly 30 years later, the effects of this tragedy continue to be felt and women remain targets because of their gender.
. 
the national day of remembrance and action on violence against women is about remembering victims; it is also a time to take action. we each have the opportunity and the responsibility to stand up against misogyny, sexism, and hate — and it starts with creating a culture of respect.
today we are reflecting on the three women who are victims of femicide in our region; wendy allan, heeley rae balanga, sandra finn. 💜🕯️🕯️🕯️💜 .
.
.
#metoo #16daysofactivism
#ksac #femicide #genderviolence #genderbasedviolence #timesup #webelievesurvivors #survivors #kawarthasexualassaultcentre

text:
steel on the skyline 
sky made of glass 
made for a real world 
all things must pass

oo-o 
waiting for something 
looking for someone 
is there no reason? 
have i stared too long?

oo-o
oo-o 
you say you'll leave me
and when the sun is low
and the rays high 
i can see it now 
i can feel it die 
oo-o
oo-o

david bowie

text:
it is not survivor's behavior, circumstances, or identity that causes gendered violence. violence against women has deep roots in societal disrespect towards women and commodification of our bodies. to end violence against women, we must challenge the very definition of masculinity.
.
.
.

all i want for christmas is my 2 front teeth 🦷! hudson is getting his first 2 chompers and they are about halfway out within a few days! this is the best pic i could get because kids but don’t let his face fool you our teething journey has been pretty much a breeze. i don’t mean it has all been 🌈 and 🦋 but compared to what is was before i had oils it is! hudson started teething at only 2 months and it was a nightmare! he was so fussy and often inconsolable, sound familiar? i was giving him teething tablets like they were candy before i found out how dangerous they were. when he was about 3 months old is when i got my starter kit and cue the angels singing👼🏼! copaiba has been my life saver when it comes to teething! i would rub one drop on his gums and instantly he was in a better mood and smiling again! i also make a “tooth fairy” 🧚‍♂️ roller with copaiba and lavender and roll it along his jawline for relief as well! i’m so glad that i have these tools to support my babe and make him feel better, as a mom there is no better feeling! .
.

text:
“venus within” 30x40” acrylic. she’s ready to leave for paris. the next time i see her will be this dec 13-16th with the snba @ carrousel du louvre. 🙏🎨please share & if you wish to support me in this endeavour just follow the link at the bottom. 🎨🙏
the paris painting ‘venus within’. which i am currently raising funds to help cover costs for participation in the 157th edition of the snba, it will be held in annex of the louvre in paris, france, taking place from 13 to 16 of december 2018. funds will be used for a variety of needs; shipping and travel fees of the artwork and for the artist to travel to the show.
the funds raised will also contribute to a whole series called ‘indestructible women’, it will be displayed here in canada later in 2019 and is what i have always wanted my art and purpose to be about. to show women and the world, that their stories of ‘indestructible women’ hold a place in history. permanently told through paint. for they are truly worthy of having their story inspire others. *please support and share*
i can do it with your help, but i can't do it alone. raising funds to be able to go with my painting to paris and to allow my other series to travel and be seen here in canada, and to especially bring it to the east coast, my home of both newfoundland and labrador. 'from labrador to paris and beyond.' go to:
https://dm2.gofund.me/from-labrador-to-paris-and-beyond

text:
hell yeah!!! 😅
*
i love to learn #kravmaga and evolve my skills of #selfdefence *
*
for me this is a huge part in #selfcare as i don’t do it for the brutality behind it. 
i take care beyond defence *
it makes me see my strength and what i want to improve/work on.
it gives me reflection where i stand in reality - that means also my limits and vulnerability. *
we don’t have to be victims - and yet we certainly will be from time to time in various - not necessarily serverely harming - ways.
*
we can learn to take care to #takeownership as much as we can.
*
can’t wait for the next grading - so eager to learn and most of all teach and give back more from here.
*
thank you to @basekmacs —> kravmaga brixton - www.krav-maga-hamburg.de - kravmaga peckham - and activeselfdefensehamburg plus @kvonloga - for your support and that i can learn from all of you!
*
*
*

text:
🤼‍♀️ smá pláss 🤼‍♀️
🤾🏾‍♀️28. þáttur 🤾🏾‍♀️ - 
konur af erlendum uppruna með claudie wilson 💫 . 
@sunna_sakana_  og @elinelisabete eru íslendingar, en u.þ.b. 12% íslendinga eru innflytjendur 🏡. konur af erlendum uppruna eru oft í viðkvæmri stöðu, eins og sást á sögum þeirra í #metoo-byltingunni ✊🏻✊🏿. þessar konur hafa oft ekki stórt félagslegt bakland og verða gjarnan fyrir fordómum 👀. í þokkabót eru þær oft háðar ofbeldismönnum sínum um skjól og jafnvel dvalarleyfi á íslandi🙅🏼‍♂️🤦🏽‍♀️🙅🏼‍♂️. gestur þáttarins er claudie wilson @claudia_ashonie , héraðsdómslögmaður, en hún flutti til íslands frá jamaíka fyrir 17 árum 🤸🏾‍♂️. hún hefur m.a. sérhæft sig í málum flóttamanna hérlendis og unnið innan samtaka kvenna af erlendum uppruna á íslandi 🏋🏽‍♀️. sunna, elín og claudie ræða um gagnkvæma aðlögun, hvernig er að vera augljós innflytjandi á íslandi 🧝🏽‍♀️, klausturmálið ⛪️🍻og hvernig íslenskar konur geta gefið erlendum konum meira pláss í sinni baráttu🗽.
þátturinn er aðgengilegur á ruv.is/null og á podcast appinu 🏄🏻‍♀️🏄🏿‍♀️🏄🏼‍♀️🏄🏾‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️ #smápláss #rúvnúll #rúv #feminist #feminism #feministpodcast #feministradio

text: #tbt. one of the first covers i ever shot. @herbritts was as safe and sweet as they come. back story is i was asked and expected to snail mail naked polaroids of my breasts in order to get the job booked. not sure what surprise they thought i had hiding but obediently i did as asked. it wasn’t unusual to have to show body parts in order to get a job back then. nor was it unusual to not be asked if you wanted to or not, let alone how that made you feel. thankfully today there are folks working hard to change that reality for industry workers. @saraziff @modelallianceny @iconicfocus thanks go out to these people. working to raise awareness and create change. i didn’t have these safeties in my time but there is movement and hope for today’s young workers.  #time4respect #enoughisenough #metoo #girlpower #timeforchange #workersrights #endporn #abolishrapeculture

text:
#tbt | the sharpshooter: i am at the hire of the united states, you could say, at the hire of god. 'there's always something deserving of being shot by the right man'. said my father, and my father's father...evil...can take any form, even a child's form. 
in 1953, america was a land were progress and bigotry galloped together towards the future. unsurprisingly, her most beloved icons were often targeted to be taken down: too much power, too much freedom is always uncomfortable. 
the sharpshooter himself has other preys other than marilyn, but she’s his number one priority. and he takes delight in revealing the alleged list that the f.b.i. compiled about her many lovers. despite the glittering facade of fame, regardless of their personal star, religion or gender (!), they shared with marilyn a lot more than one might think: they all had massive political relevance, and had to be kept under strict surveillance for the sake of the nation, and god.

_______________

text:
got to witness the most amazing panel yesterday, thanks to @leewayfound, @temple_contemp, and #reatajiri who brought our whole mfa cohort: “the pleasure principle: finding pleasure in the age of #metoo,” featuring the founder of the #metoo movement herself, @taranajaneen, in conversation with @favianna1 and moderated by @thefatsextherapist, who is my new favorite hero!! i also got to meet everybody afterwards (swipe to see fan-femme pics with tarana, sonalee, and my fellow first year @julijackson, who sat right next to me through this whole righteous thing, and shared many #fuckyeah moments with me). this is the next step in the #metoo movement - finding pleasure in our survivor bodies while we also hold and process and digest our pain. i have always, always seen pleasure as a healing act and held desire as my compass and i’m so glad to see that prominent social justice folx and connecting that to their and our movement building communities. also, tarana burke has a non-binary child, and hearing her talk about their journey together brought tears to their eyes (this was what we were connecting over in the second pic). these femmes are fierce and i highly recommend keeping an eye out for the video of this talk that will be released to the public soon. also, psa: pleasure and pain are intertwined. we may all feel broken and disconnected intermittently or permanently in our lives, and there is no right way to heal. but if we can access everyday pleasure in our daily lives we can start to build a bridge to joy. and this doesn’t mean #$elfcare spa packages; it means watching law and order in your pajamas, or cultivating awesome friendships, or wearing a sweater we feel cute in as we do the dirtier, harder work of composting this capitalist shit heap of a system that bears down on us all. and, yes, i’m a survivor, and i thank my decade+ long journey for leading me to a place of feeling really great in my body at least once a day. okay love you all 💕🥝💯
🌈
#metoo #pleasureactivism #taranaburke #faviannarodriguez #thefatsextherapist #sonaleerashatwar #leewayfoundation #templeuniversity #templecontemporary

text:
this afternoon i am feeling productive.

how often do you use “fine”, “good”, “bad” or “ok” as feeling words?  they really aren’t good descriptors of how one is feeling - they are vague and noncommittal.

some clients have shared that they use those 4 words as feeling words because they do not know what they are feeling.  or, they do not know how to identify their feelings.  some clients like more neutral words because they don’t like “bad feelings”. .

probably not too surprising, i do not view feelings as good versus bad. i think of experiencing all feelings to be important. not important because some feelings are unpleasant, but because if we don’t feel sadness, how can we really experience joy; if we don’t feel fear, how do we understand contentment; and so on. .

let’s learn to expand our feeling vocabulary!  let’s break some of our family rules (or ed rules) that we are only allowed to express certain feelings! let’s learn to identify what we are feeling and why!

this color feelings wheel was designed by dr. gloria willcox.  it can be downloaded and printed.  if identifying feelings is difficult for you, i encourage you to begin learning what you are feeling.  feelings are not as scary as we think they are.  it’s can be quite liberating to be able to identify a feeling and understand why we are feeling that way, and how to change it! 💜

#drgloriawillcox

text:
episode 20 with nubia duvall wilson, published author
📚we had a soulful conversation about her book, the survivor’s club.
🤝nubia shared her experience as a survivor of abuse and her work to help other survivors get the support they need.
💛this is the perfect book for a “book club for busy people” - it’s a short read that will lead to a big conversation. 
this episode is fully an immersion into the interview with nubia. she is candid about her experiences and all of the emotions that she felt and still feels when there is a triggering event, like the supreme court justice nomination a couple of months ago. our focus moved to mental health, having compassion for oneself and others, and coping with the strong emotions that come long after the trauma is over. we both hope that this podcast helps you understand, start a conversation, or gives you hope that you can survive and thrive after trauma. $5.00 from each book sold goes to charity:
the ny center for children
stop child predators

thank you for your continued support of sip in soma! 👉subscribe to the podcast where ever you listen to your favorite shows!

the studio is up and i am producing live shows, events, and recording the podcast at the soma general store holiday pop-up shop located at 14 south orange avenue in south orange, nj.

text:
what are the connections between #metoo, healing, sexual pleasure, orgasm, and being in fulfilling relationships? watch this video featuring a groundbreaking conversation between metoo movement founder, @taranajaneen tarana burke, and myself, moderated by sex therapist, @thefatsextherapist sonalee rashatwar. our dialogue felt so good and i emerged from our conversation feeling full, many attendees shared with us that they got ideas on how they better love themselves and bring more joy and pleasure into their lives. as people affected by systemic oppression, historical trauma and patriarchy - to claim one's joy and to be deliberate with feeling ourselves in our bodies is an act of liberation. thank you @leewayfound leeway foundation for hosting this! 
link to video: bit.ly/pleasureprinciple2018

the topics we discussed from a cis femme woc perspective included:
- relationships - sex toys
- healing from sexual assault
- strategies to practice more fulfilling relationships
- fat bodies and pleasure
- desirability
- white supremacy
- clitoral orgasm
- sex parties
- getting your body's needs met
- queer and non queer love and negotiation
- masturbation

text:
⚠️ long but super important post! ⚠️ ▪️▪️▪️▪️▪️▪️
recently, secretary of education betsy devos released new title ix guidelines.

we are concerned that the proposed guidelines provide more protections for the accused. additionally, the proposed guidelines make it more difficult for survivors of sexual violence to report harassment and assault by narrowing the definition of sexual misconduct.

all students k-12 and beyond deserve to grow up safe, respected, and valued. under these new proposals, fewer students may report gender-based violence and many will be denied equal access to education. in the wake of #metoo and #timesup, schools must do more, not less, to protect every student’s right to safety on campus.

the department of education is currently accepting feedback during its sixty-day notice and comment period, which ends in january.

we are calling on survivors, advocates, and allies to make their voices heard.

you can submit your comments online here: www.regulations.gov

or you can mail them to:

brittany bull
u.s. department of education
400 maryland avenue s.w.
room 6e310
washington, d.c. 20202

please include the docket id no. ed-2018-ocr-0064 in the reference line of your comment.

we remind our survivors and allies that submitted comments are considered public information. only include information that you are comfortable sharing publicly. ▪️▪️▪️▪️▪️▪️▪️
links about how you can save #titleix in our bio ❗

text_retweet:
😃💛 posted @withrepost • @brombergsforlag woop woop här kommer en hel drös med tips på hårda julklappar från världens bästa emma knyckare! • • • ”mot patriarkatet” av clara henry. clara är kanske det bästa som har hänt mig. hennes böcker till min 13-åriga bonusdotter är den bästa investering jag gjort. samtidigt får bonussonen läsa hampus nesvolds ”ta det som en man” och sedan kan dom byta böcker med varandra. hejja denna djupt begåvade generation som ger oss normkritiskt och underhållande diskussions-underlag hemma. • • • ”mellan raderna” av jenny nordlander. tusentals kvinnor slöt samman under #metoo, samtidigt satt jenny med färdigt manus om kvinnors villkor inom journalistbranchen. tack för denna bok. • • • ”lisbet och sambakungen” av emma karinsdotter.
emmas bok är den varmaste och roligaste bok jag läst för mitt barn. det har tillochmed varit roligt att göra läggningen. äntligen en barnbok om tokiga, rimliga vuxna som jag kunde identifiera mig med. • • • ”vi ska ha barn” av marie björk. en handbok i jämställt föräldrarskap som riktar sig till båda föräldrarna. hade vi läst denna när jag var gravid hade jag antagligen inte behövt skriva min föräldrabok ”hit med flaskan.” • • • ”det heliga jävla moderskapet” 
en samling skamlösa berättelser om moderskapet. min bibel och helt genial. en rimlig bok som alla borde få på mödravårdscentralen. • • • ”en apa i rågsved” av anna suvanna davidsson. 
annas debutroman är en skildring av en kass relation, att våga bryta upp för att tillslut våga vara sig själv utan att be om ursäkt. 
den gav mig hopp. • • • ”moder justitia” av ida eklöf. en samling texter/dikter som är roliga, rätta och smashing fantastiska. 
jag är så glad över att ha få upptäckt även lyrik. detta tack vare yolanda bohm och hennes bok ”ikon” som rätt från hjärtat daskar ut dom mest smärtsamma och roligaste orden på ett magiskt sätt.
name: Feministisk lyrik o satir  💛💪

text:
long before #metoo became the catalyst for a women’s movement about sexual assault — and a decade before the fall of #harveyweinstein, #billcosby and u.s. olympic gymnastics doctor larry nassar — there was jeffrey edward epstein.

epstein, a multimillionaire hedge fund manager whose friends included a constellation of entertainers, #politicians, business titans and royalty, for years lured teenage girls to his palm beach mansion as part of a cult-like sex pyramid scheme, police in the town of #palmbeach found.

the girls arrived, sometimes by taxi, for trysts at all hours of the day and night. few were told much more than that they would be paid to give an old man a massage — and that he might ask them to strip down to their underwear or get naked. but what began as a massage often led to masturbation, oral sex, intercourse and other sex acts, police and court records show. the alleged abuse dates back to 2001 and went on for years.

in 2007, despite ample physical #evidence and multiple witnesses corroborating the girls’ stories, federal prosecutors and epstein’s lawyers quietly put together a remarkable deal for #epstein, then 54. he agreed to plead guilty to two felony prostitution charges in state court, and in exchange, he and his accomplices received immunity from federal #sextrafficking charges that could have sent him to prison for life.

he served 13 months in a private wing of the #palmbeachcounty stockade. his alleged co-conspirators, who helped schedule his sex sessions, were never prosecuted.
(video miami herald)

#jefferyepstein #donaldtrump #billclinton #hillaryclinton #tukkit #truth #pizzagate #endit #childtrafficking #pedowood #pedogate

text:
this is my last squad of 2018. what a year it’s been…. i coached 7 different teams over the course of 12 months.
✨
3 - 2-week reboots
2 - 1 month missions
1 - 8 weeks to change
1 - greek island adventure 🇬🇷
✨
i scrolled down my feed to look at my squads and a wave of emotions came over me. i’ve seen so many women break free of their bullshit this year and become the women they were born to be.
💃🏼
my first camp was in january when all that #metoo crap went down…. we all came to camp wearing black in support of each other. we made a pact that 2018 was going to be the year of the queen!
👑
over the course of the year, there were highs and there were lows. the toughest camp i taught was in august when the world seemed to be falling apart around us. my squads are filled with women who fight…. they are rebellious, intelligent, beautiful women who do their best to add positivity and change to the world. i’m so lucky to play a part in these legends’ lives.
🙏🏼
as we close this year, the world seems to be making a comeback and i look at this final team with a smile…. 2018 truly was the year of the queen and it’s our turn to run the house.
#comebackcamps #stonetone .
.
.
#fitnessmotivation #stonetonesquad #fitspo #lsflifestyle #instafit #bootcamp #womenwholift #2018

text: been thinking about gender-based violence a lot these days (more than usual, which is a lot). a friend asked if i’d be comfortable sharing my experiences for a video production and it’s been a handful to process... i also had a nasty encounter with an acquaintance recently that resurfaced all these feelings. the statistics feel so cold and removed from the flesh and blood of the reality... they also just never seem to add up to the people i know, the stories i’ve heard. i have yet to meet a single queer person, woman, or person of trans experience that has not been the victim of either physical, emotional, psychological or sexual violence. if you know of someone, though, please let me know. i’d love to be proven wrong on this one. #genderbasedviolence #violence #stats #wtf #metoo

text:
today is national remembrance of violence against women day, so today on the blog we are highlighting our client cynthia's* story. 
it took cynthia three months to make the decision to pick up the phone and call evelyn skeete, transitional and housing support worker at yorktown. “when i called evelyn, she didn’t get into trying to make an appointment with me; she just said, ‘you are welcome to come right away.’ i went that day and met with evelyn who shared a lot of information with me. evelyn never pried. i could tell she had a lot of experience working with women who have gone through similar experiences. she was extremely knowledgeable and she meant business; i knew she could help me,” says, cynthia.

read cynthia's full story and learn more about yorktown's violence against women services by clicking the link in our bio. #myactionsmatter #metoo #yorktownfamilyservices #vaw #violenceagainstwomen
name: Yorktown Family Services

it took cynthia three months to make the decision to pick up the phone and call evelyn skeete, transitional and housing support worker at yorktown. “when i called evelyn, she didn’t get into trying to make an appointment with me; she just said, ‘you are welcome to come right away.’ i went that day and met with evelyn who shared a lot of information with me. evelyn never pried. i could tell she had a lot of experience working with women who have gone through similar experiences. she was extremely knowledgeable and she meant business; i knew she could help me,” says, cynthia.

read cynthia's full story and learn more about yorktown's violence against women services by clicking the link in our bio. #myactionsmatter #metoo #yorktownfamilyservices #vaw #violenceagainstwomen

text:
the crucible_mary warren (2/2)

hello folks, it's #monologuethursday! this week i am proposing you an excerpt from "the crucible" by arthur miller, a play based on the salem witch hunt. this is the segment in which mary warren, in order to divert the suspects lingering on her, accuses sarah good of witchcraft; miller depicts warren as a weak character, but i decided to go for a different choice: instead of simple weakness, i wanted to show the malice of cowardice, and this not just because of some supposed artistic licence, but because i believe that in hard times there is no excuse for acts like warren's. and i feel that, once again, miller's play is more contemporary then he could imagine: he wrote it as a critique against maccartism, but things haven't really changed. people keep turning in the neighbor, blaming on the weakest, on the diverse, on  immigrants, on women not even their own "sins", but sins that belong to those who command them. weakness and cowardice have always been amongst the most powerful weapons that the people simply hand to their leaders, and it has always led to disaster. and i feel that cowards are even more to blame that tyrants for that disaster, because they kill their brothers and sisters for nothing but their misareble nature.

in hard times we must stay tight, we must stick together and find the courage to defend our dignity throigh the love for each other.
always.
#agirlfromtheislandinnewyork
girlfromtheislandinnewyork

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
i know it’s the “most wonderful time of year.” but in all honesty it can be the hardest too! 
if you’ve been through stuff.... this time of year can leave you feeling : 
abandoned
heartbroken
alone
paralyzed in fear & anxiety
having weight gain
stressed to the max
experiencing sleepless nights
having serious doubts
feeling hopeless
having mental fog
feeling unworthy ** this was me **
becoming a single mom of three boys, amongst extreme circumstances left me hurting, doubting, and afraid. 
and this christmas 🎄 season stirs up a lot of raw emotions. •
i believe breakthrough happens when you first begin to understand your own worth and value. •
that is why i have created this series! •

i found practices that brought me breakthrough, healing, hope and joy, despite my darkest siutations! 
and now, i want to share it with you !! •
if you want to experience breakthrough in any area of your life >> mind body and soul << sign up
for a free 7 day series 
amiechristine.com/breakthrough/

xoxoxo ⚔️💖

text:
anger, resentment, annoyed...all feelings i’m doing some deep, deep healing on and holy sheeeeet it’s freaking hard!!! 🥺⁣
⁣
i never realized i had anger issues until i started on my spiritual healing journey a little over a year ago. and now i’m in a course where we are diving deep and clearing out all of this crud, and i’m realizing the anger is something i need to heal! ⁣
⁣
i’m not someone that goes around yelling or anything but it’s more of an annoyed anger or resentment i feel a lot. ⁣
⁣
towards danny, towards harrison, towards myself. 😢⁣
⁣
it’s an awful feeling, but i’m on the right path of releasing the lifelong holds that have formed in my soul. it feels good, it feels scary, and feels freeing to get it all out. ⁣
⁣
as i coach others on, self awareness is the first step to changing anything. ⁣
⁣
✨🦏💗🙏🏻⁣
⁣
⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣

text:
tw; rape, sexism, assault, death
•
29 years ago today (december 6, 1989) a male gunman entered l’école polytechnique in montreal canada. he walked into a lecture for engineering students and forced all of the males to leave the classroom. he then proceeded to line all of the women in the class against a wall and tell them that engineering is a mans job. he then shot and killed 14 women. this act of sexism sparked the beginning of the white ribbon campaign all around the world. by wearing a white ribbon, you are making a pledge to never commit an act of violence towards women. in 2018, the world was taken over by the me too movement which encouraged women to speak up and call out their assaulters and rapists. we do realize that this isn’t lgbtq+ related, but this is an extremely important message to be shared. if you have experienced any form of harassment or assault in your life, speak up and take a stand. there are call centers that you can contact, or you can even dm, or email us and we will help. let 2018 end all violence against women and let 2019 mark the start of a year were everyone is equal. join the pledge to end violence against women.
-the very gay teens.
•

text_retweet:
i've decided to repost this, so many of you have probably seen this before. the reasons i had for deleting my posts are not as important as the reasons i had for posting in the first place. so many of us are struggling in the same ways, and i am here to help anyone who needs it! ❤️ one day this body will be mine again. one day i will be able to look at myself and like what i see. i thought things would be better by now. i thought i would love myself and my body again. i don't. i have spent over a year feeling as if i'm in someone else's body, and it's a body i hate. i hate everything about this body. its face. its stomach. its legs. ever since i realized what you were doing to me, it's felt like there is something that has infected my body. i want to just forget everything you did and reset my life. i guess that's just what abuse and rape does to you. 
after months of struggling, i have finally realized that it isn't going away. pretending like it didn't happen won't change anything, and it won't heal me. this needs to be talked about. this is my story to tell, and keeping it a secret isn't helping anyone. i get it though. i really do. it's not a fun to topic to talk about or even hear about. i get it. it's scary to think about these things happening. to think that the people you consider heroes, close friends, or even family could do such things to you or someone else is a terrifying thought. but this is happening. it has happened, and unfortunately, it will keep happening as long as we a stay quiet. i lied to myself for a very long time about what was happening, so i get it. 
so to anyone else struggling with this, we will get through this. we will overcome what was done to us. we will rebuild and become stronger than ever, and i will be here for anyone else struggling. 
and to the person who hurt me, while you're out believing you're a hero saving lives and putting out fires, i'll be rebuilding myself from the fire you put me through, and i will come out better than ever, loving myself and my body. and one day i'll even wear my favorite clothes again ❤️ #awareness #metoo #sexualassault #survivor

text:
i can not begin to express my excitement with what it is i am doing. i believe with every fibre of my being that i am walking out the calling on my life. all glory to god. 
the vision is crystal clear.
i am championing restoration and redemption in the lives of women by speaking into and calling forth their full potential as daughters of the king.
it is a time to take the misrepresentation of the gospel that has happened over and over and wounded so many, to come to a stop. it will not only be by words, it will be by action. a new wineskin. it is time for women to stand softly and strong in who they were created to be by him, for it is what this world needs desperately.

text:
tack @knyckare & @brombergsforlag ❤️
・・・
woop woop här kommer en hel drös med tips på hårda julklappar från världens bästa emma knyckare! • • • ”mot patriarkatet” av clara henry. clara är kanske det bästa som har hänt mig. hennes böcker till min 13-åriga bonusdotter är den bästa investering jag gjort. samtidigt får bonussonen läsa hampus nesvolds ”ta det som en man” och sedan kan dom byta böcker med varandra. hejja denna djupt begåvade generation som ger oss normkritiskt och underhållande diskussions-underlag hemma. • • • ”mellan raderna” av jenny nordlander. tusentals kvinnor slöt samman under #metoo, samtidigt satt jenny med färdigt manus om kvinnors villkor inom journalistbranchen. tack för denna bok. • • • ”lisbet och sambakungen” av emma karinsdotter.
emmas bok är den varmaste och roligaste bok jag läst för mitt barn. det har tillochmed varit roligt att göra läggningen. äntligen en barnbok om tokiga, rimliga vuxna som jag kunde identifiera mig med. • • • ”vi ska ha barn” av marie björk. en handbok i jämställt föräldrarskap som riktar sig till båda föräldrarna. hade vi läst denna när jag var gravid hade jag antagligen inte behövt skriva min föräldrabok ”hit med flaskan.” • • • ”det heliga jävla moderskapet” 
en samling skamlösa berättelser om moderskapet. min bibel och helt genial. en rimlig bok som alla borde få på mödravårdscentralen. • • • ”en apa i rågsved” av anna suvanna davidsson. 
annas debutroman är en skildring av en kass relation, att våga bryta upp för att tillslut våga vara sig själv utan att be om ursäkt. 
den gav mig hopp. • • • ”moder justitia” av ida eklöf. en samling texter/dikter som är roliga, rätta och smashing fantastiska. 
jag är så glad över att ha få upptäckt även lyrik. detta tack vare yolanda bohm och hennes bok ”ikon” som rätt från hjärtat daskar ut dom mest smärtsamma och roligaste orden på ett magiskt sätt.
name: Det heliga jävla moderskapet

text:
meet my super mamá, everyone knows her in g.e.m as ms. garcía. she is currently the volunteer program director and helping me with g.e.m, while i’m away at uc berkeley. she’s the single mother that raised me with narratives of resilience and possibilities.  she introduced me to historical greats like sor juana inés de la cruz, frida kahlo, harriet tubman, rigoberta menchú, sub comandante marcos, che, berta caceres.. etc.. she did not read me bed time stories, she read me real stories, beautiful radical stories 🙌🏽.
my mother is a #metoo victim, this is why she’s a child advocate and pursued her aa in child development. she is also an autism awareness advocate, as she has worked with children with severe autism for most of her life.  my mother has always been involved in anything that speaks out for the voiceless. she was at a press conference for the assassinated women of juarez with dolores huerta (she later took my little sister and i to meet her). she returned to school at a later age, thanks to my step dad’s support.  she participated in a protest for the students killed in ayotzinapa and served as the photographer and her poetry was used as part of the message. my mom graduated from cal state la with honors, first in our family at age 39. as a proud symbol of our oaxacan and indigenous roots, she decided to walk the stage in her huaraches🌱😭. my mother is a poet, a revolutionary, an immigrant, but most importantly she is a woman of faith and has always said she’s a mother first before anything else!  i believe it’s time for her to create, to become,  to be seen.  mi madre has truly always been underpaid, but what she has provided for us has been priceless.  she will be going to the @_supermamas posada for the first time, allowing herself a long awaited night out.
thank you for being a lifetime volunteer for the voiceless madre mia 🌻. #supermama #mother #violetaluna #phenomenalwoman #phenomenallyindigenous #resilient #latina #community #mimadre #girasoles🌻#doloreshuerta  #liladowns #daughterofanimmigrant  #daughterofastrongwoman #oaxacapresente

text:
#winning #howitsdone — rep. #betoorourke (d-texas) met last month with former #presidentobama, just days after the texas democrat lost his senate race against sen. ted cruz (r), the washington post reported tuesday.
-
the meeting was held nov. 16 at obama's offices in washington, d.c., amid speculation that o'rourke could launch a white house bid for 2020.
-
o'rourke has received praise from several #obama's allies who said they see similarities between the former president and o'rourke.
-
obama has called o'rourke an "impressive young man" in a recent interview "the axe files" podcast, hosted by obama's former strategist, david axelrod.
-
"it felt as if he based his statements and his positions on what he believed," obama said of o'rourke's senate campaign. "and that, you'd like to think, is normally how things work. sadly it's not."
-
o'rourke was narrowly defeated last month in his effort to unseat cruz, but he is viewed as a possible frontrunner for the 2020 democratic nomination. he has said he is considering a presidential run.
-
one recent poll showed o'rourke trailing only former vice president #joebiden and sen. #berniesanders (i-vt.) among potential 2020 democratic candidates.
—
#equality #healthcare #metoo #truth #fuckhaters #barackobama #obama #lgbtq #historyrepeats #racism #immigration #dumptrump #fucktrump #lincoln #abrahamlincoln #betoforpresident thanks!

text:
over the past year, the metoo movement has created important dialogue around sexual assault and the culture of silence that enables sexual abuse and violence to thrive. today, bhd joins the conversation and focuses explicitly on sexual assault and violence in the black community by interviewing dr. carolyn west, an award-winning author and professor of psychology at the university of washington. during the interview, dr. west provides insight into what constitutes sexual assault, the history of sexual violence against black women, the factors that shape disclosure, and the trauma and grief associated with sexual violence. after complicating the distinction between victim and perpetrator, we discuss her latest project on the images of black women in pornography, the negative consequences of those images on women and men, and sex trafficking in the black community. we close by having a conversation about how to change the culture around sexual assault and the images of black women in the media.

text:
i am so glad for #jhtoo and to be surrounded by other likeminded, supportive people who stand up for survivors and stand up for equality. everyone who spoke and came out today is incredibly brave. i believe her. say it loud, say "me too," jhu, we're watching you. 
here is the link to the obarrio petition, which i am proud to say already has over 1,400 signatures: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1faipqlscc1i8rx9uc3cbj0bijxhkphosmzebfndk6fgbvdxxy30q2hw/viewform?fbclid=iwar1cq1lw_8mh2bkv9ymmsf-hkdg-34vhn92ohdzag9zqwyjbbjnc7_ouekk

also, here is the link to betsy devos's new proposed title ix policy. it has made a lot of significant changes which will make it easier on the perpetrators and harder on the survivors. i encourage you to look it over (and am more than happy to answer any questions about it). the public commenting period is anytime before 1/28/2019 so if you are interested in learning more about the policy and/or sharing your thoughts with the federal register about title ix, you can go to this link to provide devos with official comments about her proposed changes to title ix here anytime before 1/28/2019:  https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2018/11/29/2018-25314/nondiscrimination-on-the-basis-of-sex-in-education-programs-or-activities-receiving-federal 
#jhtoo #metoo #metoomovement

text:
1,400 public high school and middle school students in lovington, nm heard me speak today in 2 assemblies. they were wonderful! and i’m so proud of the many boys and girls who came forward for their own life changing #metoo moment today. so much courage. and i’m grateful for the brave, compassionate friends who stepped up to be a voice and a support for someone else. this is the generation our world needs!

personally, i’ll forever be inspired by the 7th grade boy who came to my book table and shared that, like me, he had always wanted to run away from home. my heart went out to him and i asked him if he still struggles with that and he said “not anymore.” so i then asked him what had helped him to overcome (assuming he meant that it was in his past) and he answered, “you.” 😭 
tears fell straight from my eyes to the tile floor. 
these speaking tours take everything i have to give, but these kids and their future are worth every pinch of it. 
thank you god for another amazing day. tomorrow morning we #breakthesilence and spread hope at another hs and ms and then a community wide awareness event in the evening. i appreciate all of your prayers and support and love. #onevoice #together

i am resilient. i am a survivor. you are resilient. you are brave. you are a survivor❤️✊🏾—-sexual violence is a reality all too many native women face, and little attention is brought to the issue. uihi is bringing attention to it and encouraging the community to do the same. today we released a report detailing the alarming statistics surrounding sexual violence against predominantly low-income or homeless native women living in seattle. 
read our bodies, our stories and participate in the journey toward healing and ending the epidemic of sexual violence against native women. 
www.uihi.org

#ourbodiesourstories #weareresilient #metoo #mmiw #decolonizedata *this report contains strong language about sexual violence against american indian and alaska native women.

if you or someone you know has been a victim of sexual violence and would like help, please utilize the resources below.

national sexual assault helpline: 800.656.hope (4673)
national domestic violence hotline: 1-800-799-7233
teen dating hotline:  866-331-9474
the stronghearts native helpline, 9am-5:30pm m-f, 844-762-8483 @urbanindianhealthinstitute

text:
fact. if we do not consciously find the time and effort to fully love ourselves and respect ourselves and we instead spend each day striving to please others and attend to others needs, our inner spirits perish bit by bit. our bodies must be recognized for the devine individualness that we posses. we are all bringing something into this world different from the next. we arrive in life at the same places from a million different
backgrounds. but no one. absolutely no one can know and interpret your self care needs more precisely than yourself. quit sacrificing your self happiness. no one needs to be a martyr for self care.  stand up for your rights. posses free will again. be proud of something. spend a little more time on something important to you. why? no goddamn why? just because is why. because everyone in this world deserves to at least love someone might as well at least love ourselves.

text:
”vart kan du inte leda den som tror att ondskan alltid finns nån annanstans?” "where can't you lead someone, who thinks evil is always somewhere else?"
.
min fina vän tar med mig för att se faust på dramaten/elverket och efteråt kan vi inte sluta prata om tankar som väckts: om maktmissbruk och habegär, om rädsla, om det att titta bort fast man ser, om det att inte lyssna fast man hör. vi pratar om gränser: för ondska, förlåtelse, för hur länge man står ut med sig själv när man inte säger ifrån. och att man, när man gör det, ofta finner sig ensam. vi pratar om straff, acceptans, att välja ståndpunkt — om hur viktigt det är, men också om hur svårt det kan vara.

vi fick en kort men fin pratstund med razmus och thèrése efteråt — de spelar zeitblom och wagner med ljuvlig fingertoppskänsla och galet mycket feeling. sammanfattning: se den. den spelas till 10 januari. länk i bion.

my beautiful friend takes me to see faust at dramaten/elverket and afterwards we can not stop talking about the thoughts provoked: about power play, the desire to have and own, about fear, about looking away although you see it, about not listening although you hear it. we talk about boundaries: for evil, forgiveness, for how long you can stand yourself when you don't speak up. and that when you do, you often end up very lonely. we talk about punishment, acceptance, about  choosing a standpoint — how important it is, and how hard it is to do.

we were given the opportunity of a short but sweet talk with razmus and thèrése afterwards — they do the parts of zeitblom and wagner, with precision and crazy amounts of feeling. in short: go see it! it plays until january 10th. link in bio.

text:
#metoo
i was molested when i was in 6th grade by my cousins uncle. i used to live in a joint family household. so, whenever he came to visit my cousins family, he would somehow manage to find me alone. at first, i didn’t know exactly what was going on or what he was trying to do, but i tried to stop him every time because i knew it wasn’t right. it wasn’t something i wore or i didn’t give him “the signal” or i didn’t ask for it. i was a fucking 12 year old kid going through puberty. he would grab my breast and twist them as hard as he can. i would try to push him away and run away from him, but nothing seemed to work. it was a feeling that i’ll never forget. i would cry in pain at night, but it wasn’t the pain of my tender breast that made me cry, it was the pain in my heavy heart. and i would ask god “why me?” then be thankful to god because i didn’t get raped. 
i finally decided to tell my mom and the look on her face was unforgettable. i can already see she felt helpless. she was silent, then i said “ammu please can i call 911 and get him arrested?” and my mom said “no.” at that very moment my heart broke into so many pieces that i became numb. it hurt the most because i felt betrayed by my own mother. she didn’t want to “ruin” my reputation or my future, especially because i didn’t have a father. she didn’t want anyone to question our family because we come from a “well known, respected family”. i was angry at my mom for couple of days, then i put myself in her shoes and saw what she was going through as a mother. my mom got scared, being a widow and an immigrant with three kids in a bengali society was not easy. my mom loves me with everything and she became my shield. so, i kept my mouth shut for all these years. 
i was contemplating if i should post this or not. i kept asking myself, what would people say? what if my future family doesn’t accept me for this? what if no one believes me? then, i realized that’s the exact reason why my mom never said anything and i didn’t want to be that person. i have every right to speak up for myself. i am more than just a body. i am strong, stronger than ever. i am a woman and that is my superpower.

text:
it has been a little over one year since the beginning of the #metoo movement. as one of the main goals of the movement is to create an environment more prone to supporting victims of sexual harassment, progress can arguably be quantified by the number of sexual harassment charges filed annually. 
compared to the 5-year average, this past year saw a significant rise in charges filed with the eeoc, increasing over 12%. similarly, lawsuits filed by the eeoc increased 50% while successful mediation proceedings rose by 43%. with stats like these i would say the movement has made some important progress so far, and i hope to see continued growth throughout 2019. 
sources: u.s. equal employment opportunity commission
name: Andrew Trick

compared to the 5-year average, this past year saw a significan not rise in charges filed with the eeoc, increasing over 12%. similarly, lawsuits filed by the eeoc increased 50% while successful mediation proceedings rose by 43%. with stats like these i would say the movement has made some important progress so far, and i hope to see continued growth throughout 2019. 
sources: u.s. equal employment opportunity commission

text: this leaf is my leaf. ✨🌱 the first survivor leaf entry i wrote one night when i couldn’t sleep. all three of my stories are written here. i’m proud of this leaf. while each of these experiences was born in pain, i have come so far since these darknesses in my life. i’ve pushed through fear, anxiety, shame, guilt- and i’m still here. gone are shame and guilt (i’m still working on fear and anxiety, and that’s okay. work is progress!), and i’ve finally found a way to come back into the light. survivorship is something that never goes away- i’ll never be able to erase these memories.  but i have transformed their power over me. i painted, i wrote, i created, and i grew them into something beautiful. i was recently speaking to a friend and fellow survivor and told her that, while there have been times in my past that i have felt empowered *in spite of* being a survivor, i have never felt empowered *because* i am a survivor- until now. this work is changing me. ✨🌱 click the link in my bio to contribute your story to the survivor tree. #rapesurvivor #survivor #survivoradvocate #survivorselfcare #metoo #whyididntreport #drchristineblaseyford #endrapeculture #believewomen #believesurvivors #believeblackwomen #timesup #artist #wip #workinprogress #thesurvivortreeproject

text:
⁉️ men. boys. think we know what women have to deal with everyday?!?!⠀
⠀
today is national day of remembrance and action on violence against women.⠀
⠀
unlike other events about taking action against violence against women, today is different. it’s organized by us, men. in fact, it is the world’s largest movement of men and boys working to end violence against women. ⠀
⠀
“uhm michael... this isn’t the usual personal development shii you post. this is weir-“⠀
⠀
weird? this?! this is weird to you?!? you cannot be serious. okay. let me explain as best i can as a guy.⠀
⠀
working to fight a system that frequently puts you at a disadvantage is exhausting. explaining over and over what consent is, trying to navigate life without getting harassed as much, having to insist that the pay gap exists when you have actual stats to back you up. that’s a lot and it’s just the tip of the iceberg.⠀
⠀
women do this every day. and us men? we only have to engage with this work when, we want to. if we’re tired and need a break we can just take it whereas women can’t- not without risking their safety, personal comfort, or inadvertently perpetuating the entire fucked up system.⠀
⠀
it’s important that we do part of the work, so that if they need a break, they can take it too. if someone catcalls my girlfriend while we’re walking down the street- it might be nice for her if sometimes i’m the one to call him out so that she doesn’t for the 400th+ time (cuz she the fkn bomb and beautiful af).⠀
⠀
anecdotal evidence aside (looking at you faith goldy) the facts (yes, facts, proven by research) will tell you that women are not yet equal in our society. so it’s time to step up guys.⠀
⠀
join the club. and not just for one day a year.

text_retweet:
#repost @jacquelyn.lee with @get_repost
・・・
hello, loves! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
i’m working on a new project to be launched in october for #domesticviolenceawarenessmonth. and i need your help. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
the focus of this project is to bring awareness to victim-blaming. it’s something that i’m extremely passionate about. i personally was victim-blamed a countless amount of times. as a victim-turned-advocate, i feel the need to shed light upon this topic. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
i can go on and on about my story, but it is not enough. in order to make a difference— the world needs to hear your stories, too. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
if you are a survivor: have you ever been victim-blamed? what was specifically said and/or done to you? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
in the comments below, tell me exactly what was said to you, quote-on-quote by someone who didn’t believe your survivor story. this is open to anyone who has been the victim of domestic violence, child abuse and/or sexual assault. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
to give some examples: ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
“you weren’t abused. give me a break.”⁣⁣
⁣⁣
“he only hit you once. big deal.”⁣⁣
⁣⁣
“but, what did you do to provoke him to do that?” ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
these are all examples of victim-blaming/victim-shaming. have similar words been said to you? if so, please contribute to this project. use your voice. tell your story. let’s put an end to victim-shaming. ⁣⁣
⁣
thank you. ⁣
⁣⁣
• • • ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

⁣⁣

text:
their waiting room is cozy and they have fresh coffee. the desk people smiled, but not in that weird way. 
i could easily move forward in my life and not work through these things.
i'm addressing my #mst experience because i realized how much it impacted me. it impacted relationships with myself and others, my ability to know what safe is, to choose healthy people to be around, to be kind to myself, to feel as if my body was my own, how i felt about #integrity, the #military, christianity, and #america.
it changed my life path. i need to look at that. i want to. 
i want to level up in life. 
#mst #armyofone #lifeismessy #newnormal #youareworthit #rapeculture #metoo #veteran #metoomilitary #timesup

“justice will not be served until those who are unaffected are as outraged as those who are."
this video was filmed & edited by me to spread awareness and share the stories of these women that were murdered or still missing since 1969. 
i first came across this bridge of red ribbons in midtown toronto, a few months back during my morning run. i started to read their stories and from that moment on i knew i had to do a video to honour these women that have lost their lives. please research the #mmiw #mmiwg #redribbon #reddressproject movement, feel free to repost this video, share their stories, and cause more awareness for our women in north america. we have not forgotten you. justice needs to be served. 🙏🏾 for full video, click the link in bio 📽 #missingmurderedindigenouswomen #highwayoftears #nativelivesmatter #itstartswithus #indigenouslivesmatter #weneedjustice #amberalyssatuccaro #britishcolumbia #ashleysimpson #bringashleyhome #salmonarm #alberta #quebec #missingperson #firstnations #indigenous #metoo #kaygardnerbeltline #stclairandyonge #canada #indigenouswomenrise #notinvisible #walkingwithoursisters #nationalinquiry #womensconvention #metoo @indigwomenrise @grownupnavajo @femmagradio @ndpcanada @womensmarch

"i was about 14 years old, travelling in the bus with a friend after school for the first time on our own. we were excited as this was a little adventure to us. the excitement didn't last long however, when we were approached by an elderly man. he was standing behind us and first started by attempting to talk to us, to which we ignored. he then whispered lewd, explicit comments which subsequently lead to him pushing against and rubbing his genitals on me. i froze with fear. i couldn't move nor confront him. i became completely numb. my friend realized what was happening but i knew she was too scared to react. tears started rolling down my face and i felt helpless. this act continued for a while and finally when a lady noticed, and offered me her seat, the perpetrator got off the bus. none of the bystanders intervened, and for days i couldn't overcome my fear. i was traumatized. i didn't tell my parents, thinking they would never allow me to travel in a bus again, nor spoke to my friends as i was ashamed. my friend and i promised each other that this would be a secret. little did i know then, that all my life i would have to go through similar experiences whenever i use public transport" - janani.

if you witness sexual harassment in public transport: intervene. speak up. be the change.

text:
me. it's all about me tonight!

this journey of self care has been long awaited. i'm a recovering people pleaser and survivor of narcissist abuse. so it was always about other people, and i came second. not anymore. not to be self absorbed, but to make sure i'm taken care of so i can love others, and be my best me.

if you aren't practicing self love and self care, i encourage you to start now. whether it be big or small, just start. your body and mind deserve it.

still a queen 👑✊.
.
.
.

#repost @af3irmsf

day 12 - repost from @m.mariposa__ 
when i was a brand new teacher, trash ass male teachers tried to go about their trash ass ways. within the first month at my new school i had been targeted by a upper grade teacher who thought i was the one - thought i would allow his behavior. i was at a loss as to how most effectively address the situation since i was the newbie. what i’ve learned is that a lot of men will make light of trespasses unless you threaten their livelihood. so i did. i wrote a detailed email to my principal and my union rep. see next image, feel free to use as template if you need to (i left the name bc idgaf, also some typos my b). no matter the field, no matter the level of education, women are continuously subjugated to deal with harassment in our day-to-day lives. i’m done with male entitlement and lukewarm allies that say nothing. do better. 💜@af3irmsf participates in 16 days of activism to amplify the voices of women of color impacted by gender-based violence. we recognize that harassment is a prevalent problem in women of color’s everyday lives because of rape culture, colonial legacies of violence, our fetishization, and our presumed accessibility. today and every day we say “stop. that was harassment.” #16daysofactivism #notyourfetish #metoo #hearmetoo #af3irm

text:
it is official this saturday 12/8 at @flowerpowercoffeehousenyc the @shewillspeakseries and @wide.eyes.publishing will host their first event and apart of event proceeds will go to end rape on campus (eroc @endrapeoncampus) which works to end campus sexual violence through direct support for survivors and their communities; prevention through education; and policy reform at the campus, local, state, and federal levels.

i would personally like to thank @endrapeoncampus for speaking with me and really understanding what the @shewillspeakseries is trying to accomplish! i would also like to thank @endrapeoncampus for all the work they are doing! as a survivor it inspires me to see organizations that truly are there to create reform and elevate survivors voices. so make sure you come out and if you cannot we are working on how you can support/donate right now 🙏🏽

text: let’s talk being a woman..and the mother of a daughter... i am a woman. being a woman is a battle worth fighting. being a woman is more then what we are told. being a woman is empowering and discouraging all at the same time. being a woman is beautiful and heartbreaking. being a woman is not unfortunate. being a woman is not about settling for less than what you deserve in all aspects. being a woman is not an invitation for you to tear me apart because of my body type, my outfit, or how i present myself. being a woman does not mean you can look at me like an object, or take my “no” as a “yes”. being a woman is not what you want it to be. being a woman is what i am and how i want to be. i am a mother and woman who plans to raise my daughter to be who and what she wants to be. i will never say “you can’t” because she can. i will never say her “no” means nothing, when i’m fact her “no” means exactly that. i will always love her and be an example for her. i will always embrace her beauty, from the inside out and teach her to embrace her flaws. i will always remind her that being a woman is an amazing and empowering thing. ❤️
name: Her Journey In The Raw

text:
выкатили ежегодный youtube rewind 2018

для тех, кто не знает, что это вообще такое: youtube приглашает самых популярных блогеров, стримеров(на ютубе), а так же не менее популярных боку и жоку и снимает с ними видео, а в итоге каждый раз получается говно, на которое выливают тонны хейта в комментах и дизлайков, ютуб пытается анально огораживаться, чистить комменты, но каждый раз не выходит.

в этот раз упомянули жанр года - battle royale, конечно же показали ninja (самый высокооплачиваемый стример, основную популярность получил благодаря стримам fortnite на пару с нигра-реперами), рассказали про права инвалидов, конечно же #metoo и #мояборьба, а так же уилл смитт на заставочке. 
лучше чем в прошлый раз, но опять без pewdiepie. благодаря новой функции "премьерных показов" — у видео на ютубе теперь есть чат, угадайте что ютуб сделал? правильно — в чате только удобные и одобренные посты, а в комментах чистят весь хейт. колесо сансары дало оборот.

text:
gah! had to jump on here again and share about @dressember day 6! we spent a gorgeous evening in dc celebrating the life work of mark holden and this lady, alice johnson on criminal justice reform. you may remember alice’s story. she was sentenced to life without parole for a non violent drug offense and was recently set free thanks in large part to the advocacy of @kimkardashian. 🌱
.
.
.
alice, and many others like her find their voice and hope in @prisonfellowship academies across the country. 🌱
.
.
.
so grateful to be a part of this team! it makes me think of the quote from @hamiltonmusical: “but we will never be truly free until those in bondage are as free as you and me.” 🌱
.
.
.

text:
#춥다 아침에 눈떠서 세수만 하고 그냥 아무거나 껴입고 카페에서 구성안 쓰다가... 도무지 안 가면 맘이 불편할 것 같아서 또 왔다. #안희정 #성폭력사건 #항소심 지난 주에 이어서 오늘도 #공판심리기일 공판 절차를 협의하고 증거목록 제출 등등을 하는 날인데 재판부의 성향도 파악하고 앞으로의 방향도 볼 수 있으니까 왔다. 
굳이 내가, 그냥 개인일 뿐인데 굳이 이러고 다녀야 하나 싶지만... 일을 하면서 최근의 #metoo 덕을 보고 살기 때문에 가능하면 용기내준 고발자 분들께 나도 작으나마 배경이 되어드리고 싶다. 그리고 무엇보다... 나도 꽤 지랄맞은 안희정 지지자였으므로... 잘못된 사람을 지지한 책임을 아직 갚아가야 하니까. 
이번 항소심에 약간의 희망을 걸고 있다. 담당 재판부의 #홍동기부장판사 가 올해 초에 성평등에 기여한 #디딤돌 판결로 꼽혔기도 하고 지난 1차 심리기일 때 부터 비교적 상식적인 발언을 많이 했다. 
그러니까 1심의 #조병구 (개ㅅ...) 씨가 재판 비공개를 요청하는 피해자측 변호인들에게 “형사재판은 공개가 원칙이라..” 고 하던 것과 달리, 2심에서는 비공개 요청을 받아들여서... 증거 재출 절차에서 이렇게... 방청객을 쫓아냄. (제가 지금 쫓겨났다는 이야기..;;) 피해자의 사생활 노출, 그로인한 2차 피해를 충분히 경계하고 있다는 듯, 비공개를 선언하면서 성폭력특별법의 조항을 읊으셨는데 못 들었다. 
제발... #metoo 는 이제껏 너무 많은 여자들이 죽고, 또 침묵한 이후에 찾아온, 얻어낸 새로운 국면이다. 
우리는 이제 한 명도 더 잃을 수 없고 더이상 질 수도 없다. 
#우리는_김지은씨를_지지합니다 
#안희정이_무죄면_사법부는_유죄다

stop_filter_tweet: 아침에 눈떠서 세수만 하고 그냥 아무거나 껴입고 카페에서 구성안 쓰다가 ... 도무지 안 가면 맘이 불편할 것 같아서 또 왔다 . 지난 주에 이어서 오늘도 공판 절차를 협의하고 증거목록 제출 등등을 하는 날인데 재판부의 성향도 파악하고 앞으로의 방향도 볼 수 있으니까 왔다 . 굳이 내가 , 그냥 개인일 뿐인데 굳이 이러고 다녀야 하나 싶지만 ... 일을 하면서 최근의 덕을 보고 살기 때문에 가능하면 용기내준 고발자 분들께 나도 작으나마 배경이 되어드리고 싶다 . 그리고 무엇보다 ... 나도 꽤 지랄맞은 안희정 지지자였으므로 ... 잘못된 사람을 지지한 책임을 아직 갚아가야 하니까 . 이번 항소심에 약간의 희망을 걸고 있다 . 담당 재판부의 가 올해 초에 성평등에 기여한 판결로 꼽혔기도 하고 지난 1차 심리기일 때 부터 비교적 상식적인 발언을 많이 했다 . 그러니까 1심의 ( 개ㅅ ... ) 씨가 재판 비공개를 요청하는 피해자측 변호인들에게 “ 형사재판은 공개가 원칙이라.. ” 고 하던 것과 달리 , 2심에서는 비공개 요청을 받아들여서 ... 증거 재출 절차에서 이렇게 ... 방청객을 쫓아냄 . ( 제가 지금 쫓겨났다는 이야기.. ; ; ) 피해자의 사생활 노출 , 그로인한 2차 피해를 충분히 경계하고 있다는 듯 , 비공개를 선언하면서 성폭력특별법의 조항을 읊으셨는데 못 들었다 . 제발 ... 는 이제껏 너무 많은 여자들이 죽고 , 또 침묵한 이후에 찾아온 , 얻어낸 새로운 국면이다 . 우리는 이제 한 명도 더 잃을 수 없고 더이상 질 수도 없다 .

text:
kasus kekerasan seksual semakin lama semakin banyak, korban terus berjatuhan.
komnas perempuan mencatat kasus kasus ini jumlahnya semakin meningkat tiap tahunnya. 
forum pengada layanan juga mencatat korban melapor datang setiap hari. 
karena itu, butuh solidaritas kita bersama, gerak kita bersama untuk menuntaskan masalah ini. 
ayo dorong dpr untuk segera membahas dan mengesahkan ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual. karena bila tidak, saya, kamu, kita semua, dan orang yang kita sayangi bisa menjadi korban.

text:
at least two of the country's biggest radio operators — rogers media and bell media — say they've decided to pull the controversial christmas favourite out of their rotations this year.
that comes as the duet, written back in 1944, faces renewed scrutiny over what some say are inappropriate lyrics in the wake of the #metoo movement.
earlier this week, cleveland radio station wdok-fm announced it was no longer playing the song in response to listener feedback. some took issue over lyrics where one singer is trying to persuade the other to stay inside, with exchanges that include, "what's in this drink?" and "baby, don't hold out."
bell media spokesman scott henderson says the company, which runs two 24-hour christmas stations in vancouver and ottawa, chose not to include the christmas tune on its playlists this year.
"the song wasn't scheduled for airplay on any bell media radio stations and there are no plans to play it in the future," he wrote in an emailed statement.

source: huffingtonpost.ca

text:
look into my eyes he tells her
i’m gonna say goodbye he says yea
do not cry she begs of him goodbye yea
all that day she thinks of his love yea

they whip him through the streets and alleys there
the gormless and the baying crowd right there
they can’t get enough of that doomsday song
they can’t get enough of it all

listen

listen to the whores he tells her
he fashions paper sculptures of them
then drags them to the river‘s bank in the cart
their soggy paper bodies wash ashore in the dark
and the priest stiff in hate now demanding fun begin
of his women dressed as men for the pleasure of that priest

here i am
not quite dying
my body left to rot in a hollow tree
its branches throwing shadows
on the gallows for me
and the next day
and the next
and another day

ignoring the pain of their particular diseases
they chase him through the alleys chase him down the steps
they haul him through the mud and they chant for his death
and drag him to the feet of the purple headed priest

first they give you everything that you want
then they take back everything that you have
they live upon their feet and they die upon their knees
they can work with satan while they dress like the saints
they know god exists for the devil told them so
they scream my name aloud down into the well below

here i am
not quite dying
my body left to rot in a hollow tree
its branches throwing shadows
on the gallows for me
and the next day
and the next
and another day

listen

david bowie

text:
today, i finished ‘south of forgiveness’, by thordis elva and thomas stranger. *disclaimer* sandi toksvig praised it and i’m obsessed with her.
.
.
there are 7,200 seconds in two hours. cape town is the rape capital of the world. 7/10 rapes are committed by someone known to the victim.
.
.
this controversial collaboration is a book for everyone.
.
.
possibly the most important thing i shall read this year. i cannot begin to comprehend the lasting implications someone feels having been subjected to sexual violence. this book has however, shown me both the stark reality of it within our society, and the catastrophic effects upon both the survivor and perpetrator.
.
.
whilst reading this book i’ve had various conversations with male and female friends about sexual violence within our current culture. 
how much do we know? 
what are we doing to tackle it? 
is it deeply rooted within inequality?
.
.
this stunning narrative through the spectacular sites of cape town presents the inescapable truth that your place within society dictates whether or not you can even report the crime that you’ve been subjected to.
.
.
the level of honesty within this book has completely and utterly astounded me. we’re all vulnerable. with the #metoo and #timesup movements are we entering a society ready to change?
.
.
thank you @thordiselva 
#southofforgiveness #thursdaythoughtswithhannah #thordiselva #bookshelf #bookreview

text:
stable talk | peace, participation and patriarchy

speaker | dr. swarna rajagopalan : political scientist, consultant and writer.

curated by | @warhorse_wh 
giving her audience a thorough run-down on patriarchy from an academic sense and from a perspective of daily life. she explained the features of patriarchy (privilege, entitlement, impunity and exclusion) and how patriarchy sets up imaginary binaries. she also made a profound and convincing argument about how patriarchy is equivalent to violence. the talk concluded with her explaining on how to go about handling the #metoo movement.

text_retweet:
#repost @thecaloriedoctor ・・・
if i had the “perfect” body throughout history, this is what i’d look like.
.
mid 2010s-2018 - big butts, wide hips, tiny waists, and full lips are in! there is a huge surge in plastic surgery for butt implants thanks to instagram models posting “belfies”. 🍑 even cosmetic surgery doctors have become ig-famous for reshaping women. between 2012-2014, butt implants and injections rise by 58%.
.
mid 90s-2000s - big boobs, flat stomachs, and thighs gaps are in. in 2010, breast augmentation is the highest performed cosmetic surgery in the united states. 👙 it’s the age of the victoria’s secret angel. she’s tall, thin, and she’s always got long legs and a full chest.
.
early 90s - thin is in. having angular bone structure, looking emaciated, and super skinny is what’s dominating the runways and the magazine covers. there’s even a name for it: “heroin chic”.
. 
1950s - the hourglass shape is in. ⏳ elizabeth taylor‘s 36-21-36 measurements are the ideal. marilyn monroe’s soft voluptuousness is lusted after. women are advertised weight gaining pills to fill themselves out. playboy magazine and barbie are created in this decade.
.
1920s - appearing boyish, androgynous and youthful, with minimal breasts, and a straight figure is in! unlike the “gibson girl” of the victorian era, women are choosing to hide their curves, and are doing so by binding their chests with strips of cloth to create that straight figure suitable for flapper dresses.
.
1400-1700 the italian renaissance - looking full with a rounded stomach, large hips, and an ample bosom is in. being well fed is a sign of wealth and status. only the poor are thin.
.
why do we treat our bodies like we treat fashion? “boobs are out! butts are in!” well, the reality is, manufacturing our bodies is a lot more dangerous than manufacturing clothes. 
embrace your body because it is your own perfect body. ♥️
.
.
.
credits : @blogilates
name: Murmuration

text:
look into my eyes he tells her
i’m gonna say goodbye he says yea
do not cry she begs of him goodbye yea
all that day she thinks of his love yea

they whip him through the streets and alleys there
the gormless and the baying crowd right there
they can’t get enough of that doomsday song
they can’t get enough of it all

listen

listen to the whores he tells her
he fashions paper sculptures of them
then drags them to the river‘s bank in the cart
their soggy paper bodies wash ashore in the dark
and the priest stiff in hate now demanding fun begin
of his women dressed as men for the pleasure of that priest

here i am
not quite dying
my body left to rot in a hollow tree
its branches throwing shadows
on the gallows for me
and the next day
and the next
and another day

ignoring the pain of their particular diseases
they chase him through the alleys chase him down the steps
they haul him through the mud and they chant for his death
and drag him to the feet of the purple headed priest

first they give you everything that you want
then they take back everything that you have
they live upon their feet and they die upon their knees
they can work with satan while they dress like the saints
they know god exists for the devil told them so
they scream my name aloud down into the well below

here i am
not quite dying
my body left to rot in a hollow tree
its branches throwing shadows
on the gallows for me
and the next day
and the next
and another day

listen

david bowie

text:
@thejimmydoreshow @bbcnews @nbcnews @anakasparianofficial @turunsanomat wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

🎅 ”the sexy santa exhibition” på frilagret! 🎅
🎨 det bjuds på julkänsla med mörka förtecken, när konstnären @camillajamting.art ställer ut  på frilagret 7–14 december. ett koncept som med humor och pricksäkerhet utmanar oss att se jultomten ur nya perspektiv. vi träffade camilla. läs hela intervjun på hemsidan! 💻
✍️ berätta om din utställning!
– sexy santa är en självupptagen lättklädd tomte och i utställningen får besökaren följa med i något som föreställer en blandning av hans mancave och medvetande. jag ville ge igen på alla åldrade gubbar som sexualiserar och trakasserar unga tjejer, något som jag själv upplevt vid flera tillfällen. det var i samband med förra höstens #metoo-rörelse som jag började fundera på hur det kunde se ut i huvudet på en sådan gubbe. resultatet blev en sexig jultomte och efter hand även denna utställning som jag hoppas ska fylla besökaren med både humor och en känsla av obehag.

text:
@radiohelsinki @katyturnbc @huffpostitalia @foxnews for those 87 million people probably wondering what was actually done with their data, i went back to christopher wylie, the ex-cambridge analytica employee who blew the whistle on the company’s problematic operations in the observer. according to wylie, all you need to know is a little bit about data science, a little bit about bored rich women, and a little bit about human psychology.

step one, he says, over the phone as he scrambles to catch a train: - when you’re building an algorithm, you first need to create a training set. that is: no matter what you want to use fancy data science to discover, you first need to gather the old-fashioned way. before you can use facebook likes to predict a person’s psychological profile, you need to get a few hundred thousand people to do a 120-question personality quiz.

the “training set” refers, then, to that data in its entirety: the facebook likes, the personality tests, and everything else you want to learn from. most important, it needs to contain your “feature set”: - the underlying data that you want to make predictions on, wylie says. - in this case, it’s facebook data, but it could be, for example, text, like natural language, or it could be clickstream data – the complete record of your browsing activity on the web. - those are all the features that you want to [use to] predict. at the other end, you need your target variables, the things that you’re trying to predict for. so in this case, personality traits or political orientation, or what have you.

alex hern
the guardian

text:
@radiohelsinki @katyturnbc @huffpostitalia @foxnews bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
our second script-development #workshop took place in #kathmandu at the end of november. with us we had #theatre practitioners and veterans, visual and performance artists, and slam poets—many of whom have been working on #genderbasedviolence and the lives of women in different ways. 
the discussions were strongly influenced by the #nirmalapant rape and murder case which has had #nepal in a ferment since july. the participants drew parallels between the #impunity of the government in current democratic nepal and the impunity of the royal family in the case of the #namitasunitahatyakando when nepal was a constitutional monarchy, 37 years ago. across a gulf of over thirty years, the same hush-up, mass #protests and no solution. 
we discussed how violence exists on a continuum—from the extreme #violence of #rape to the ordinariness of #streetharassment. 
this video has yukta of @wordwarriorsnepal talking about #streetharassment, taking #publictransport and the tendency of male friends to react with #notallmen in a #metoo world. 
we'll be releasing more material from the workshop over the next few weeks so stay tuned for more #exitimpunity. 
in the meantime, tell us your thoughts on what yukta says here. do you also feel like anyone can be a harasser? if you're a man, how do you react to remarks like this? how do you feel about the continuous self-monitoring and self-regulation we often do as women occupying public space?

#zubaanbooks #endsexualviolence #breakthesilence #feminist #theatre #feministart #womensrights #feministpractice #impunity #accesstojustice #feminism
name: Zubaan
tweet_full:
our second script-development #workshop took place in #kathmandu at the end of november. with us we had #theatre practitioners and veterans, visual and performance artists, and slam poets—many of whom have been working on #genderbasedviolence and the lives of women in different ways. 
the discussions were strongly influenced by the #nirmalapant rape and murder case which has had #nepal in a ferment since july. the participants drew parallels between the #impunity of the government in current democratic nepal and the impunity of the royal family in the case of the #namitasunitahatyakando when nepal was a constitutional monarchy, 37 years ago. across a gulf of over thirty years, the same hush-up, mass #protests and no solution. 
we discussed how violence exists on a continuum—from the extreme #violence of #rape to the ordinariness of #streetharassment. 
this video has yukta of @wordwarriorsnepal talking about #streetharassment, taking #publictransport and the tendency of male friends to react with #notallmen in a #metoo world. 
we'll be releasing more material from the workshop over the next few weeks so stay tuned for more #exitimpunity. 
in the meantime, tell us your thoughts on what yukta says here. do you also feel like anyone can be a harasser? if you are a man, how do you react to remarks like this? how do you feel about the continuous self-monitoring and self-regulation we often do as women occupying public space?

#zubaanbooks #endsexualviolence #breakthesilence #feminist #theatre #feministart #womensrights #feministpractice #impunity #accesstojustice #feminism
